<DESCRIPT>  FAMILY; RECREATION  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  THIS is a big week with the Santa Clara County Fair opening Thursday and the
Gilroy Garlic Festival starting Friday.;    But for today try the
Connoisseur's Marketplace in Menlo Park featuring, along Santa Cruz Avenue,
culinary samplings from 25 restaurants and California wines and beers.
Entertainment runs 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. today at the El Camino Stage, corner of
El Camino Real and Santa Cruz Avenue and the Fremont Park Stage, corner of
University and Santa Cruz avenues. Both stages will be surrounded by white
umbrella tables and chairs. Two hundred artisans will show their creations.
Also featured are a petting zoo, clowns, face painting and art demonstrations.
Free admission and parking.;    (check) Also on tap is the California Country
Music Association, giving a family-oriented country barbecue and picnic from 2
to 6 p.m. today at Pleasure Living Connection, a new Western theme park on
Felter Road, Milpitas. Activities and live music, with a special appearance by
the Country Travelers. Admission is $5 and the chicken barbecue is $5.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  GOOD DAY FOR FAIR PLAY  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The Family Clipboard
Things to do  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     (check) A sneak preview of the Santa Clara County Fair opens from 5 to 11
p.m. Thursday with two hours of free carnival rides from 5 to 7 p.m. Admission
for all ages is $4 Thursday only. Greg Kihn Band entertains at 7 and 9 p.m.
Thursday at the amphitheater; Monster Truck Madness can be seen at 8 p.m.
Thursday at the grandstand. "Childhood Memories" is the theme for this year's
edition, which has many new attractions including the Gold Heist Stunt Show, a
Kids' Korral, Jeff Allen's Magic Windows and elephant rides.;    Nightly
fireworks, animals, foods, a petting zoo, carnival and kiddie rides, contests
and entertainment will keep the fairgrounds hopping through Aug. 11.;   
Special dates to remember: kids' days July 30 and Aug. 6, when kids 16 and
under are free from noon to 5 p.m.; and noon to 5 p.m., Tuesdays through
Fridays, when park admission plus $9 buys unlimited carnival rides.;   
Regular fair hours are noon to 11 p.m. weekdays, 11 a.m. to 11 p.m. Saturdays
and Sundays and 11 a.m. to 8 p.m. Sunday, Aug. 11. Admission is $6.50 general
(ages 17-59), $4 seniors (60 and over) and children (5 and under) and $20
family (admits up to six members). Uniformed military are free. The
fairgrounds are at 344 Tully Road, San Jose. Call (408) 295-3050 for details.;
   (check) The Gilroy Garlic Festival opens Friday for a three-day run of
gourmet garlic dishes, four stages of entertainment, demonstrations, exhibits,
mariachis, clowns and puppets. Hours are 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Friday and 10 a.m.
to 6 p.m. Saturday and next Sunday. Located at Christmas Hill Park, Tenth and
Miller avenues, Gilroy. Admission Friday is $7 adults, $2 children and
seniors, and on Saturday and Sunday, $8 adults, $2 seniors and children.;   
(box) Other family activities this week include:;    Events; An All You Can
Eat Ice Cream Social  will be held 1:30 to 4:30 p.m. next Sunday at the
Community School of Music and Arts, 253 Martens Ave., Mountain View. Featured
will be samplings from Dreyer's, Double Rainbow, Baskin-Robbins, yogurt from
J. Higby's, toppings from Smucker's, a children's art exhibit and a sound
sampler for kids to try out musical instruments. Advance tickets are $4
adults, $2.50 children; at the gate, $5 adults, $3 children, with family
attendance not to exceed $15. (415) 961-0342.;    Summer Dog Show.  The San
Mateo Kennel Club will hold its show 8:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. today at the Cow
Palace, Geneva Avenue and Santos Street, Daly City. Free admission.;    The
Summer Symphony Pops in the Park  is slated for next Sunday at Frost
Amphitheater, Stanford University. Nancy Wilson will be featured this year
with Denis De Coteau conducting the San Francisco Ballet Orchestra in a
benefit for the Children's Health Council. Gates open at 3 p.m. for picnic
goers. Live music by Take Four, a barbershop quartet, and Zigzag Walk, a jazz
band. The symphony program starts at 5 p.m. Box lunches and refreshments will
be available. $15 lawn seating, $20 chair seating with $3 off for children and
seniors or a $35 sponsor ticket. Tickets are available at the gate next Sunday
or in advance by calling (415) 326-0643.;    Entertainment; "The Princess and
the Magic Pea."  A musical adaptation of a popular fairy tale. Performers are
ages 9-16. Curtain times are 4:30 p.m. today, 7:30 p.m. Friday and Saturday,
and 4:30 next Sunday, the last day of the play's run. Alameda Children's
Musical Theatre, 1912 Central Ave., Alameda. Admission is $7; $5 for seniors,
teens, military personnel and disabled people; $4 children under 12. For
reservations call (415) 521-6965.;    Exhibits;  Children's Discovery Museum 
announces new summer hours of 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Wednesday through Saturdays;
to 8 p.m. Thursdays; and noon to 5 p.m. Sundays through Aug. 27. Tuesdays the
museum is open to pre-booked youth groups only. The museum features hands-on
exhibits and programs. Located at Woz Way and Auzerais Street, San Jose.
Admission is $6 adults, $3 children (ages 4-18); 3 and under are free. (408)
298-5437.;    Upcoming; Ringling Bros. and Barnum &amp; Bailey Circus  is
scheduling its Bay Area appearances for Aug. 20-27 at the Oakland Coliseum and
Aug. 29-Sept. 2 at the Cow Palace, Daly City. Tickets range from $8.50-$12.50,
available by calling (408) 998-2277, (415) 762-2277.  </TEXT>
